{"lexicon" 1
 "id" "com.etzhayyim.shomei.personhoodCredential"
 "description" "The AGGREGATE believer credential \u2014 a W3C-Verifiable-Credential-data-model-shaped record that rolls up a DID's verified identityClaims into an Identity Assurance Level (IAL) + proof-of-personhood signal. Per ADR-2606072100 (shomei). This is the passport-equivalent ARTIFACT: a single presentable credential proving how strongly a DID's identity is established, derived deterministically from the set of verified factors. **G3 no-PII**: contains NO personal identifiers \u2014 only `subjectDidHash` (blake2b), the SET of verified factorKinds, factor/class counts, IAL, and the proof-of-personhood boolean. **G8 identity-assurance-NOT-social-credit (CRITICAL)**: this measures how strongly identity is PROVEN, never personal worth, behavior, reputation, or rank. There is no behavioral input and no per-person ordering. **G1/G7**: for IAL \u2264 3 the credential is SELF-issued (issuer = subject; anyone re-derives it from the public claims); IAL 4 (government-verified) is Council-attested per ADR-2605260000 and is the only level the server-side gov path touches (gated)."
 "defs" {"main" {"type" "record"
 "key" "tid"
 "record" {"type" "object"
 "additionalProperties" false
 "required" ["subjectDidHash"
 "assuranceLevel"
 "verifiedFactors"
 "distinctClasses"
 "factorCount"
 "proofOfPersonhood"
 "issuer"
 "issuanceDate"]
 "properties" {"subjectDidHash" {"type" "string"
 "description" "Blake2b-256 (base64url) of the subject DID (same convention as com.etzhayyim.gov.procedure.auth.didTrustAttestation). Privacy-preserving linkage; a holder of the DID can recompute and confirm."
 "maxLength" 64}
 "assuranceLevel" {"type" "integer"
 "enum" [0
 1
 2
 3
 4]
 "description" "Identity Assurance Level. 0=did-only (no verified factor). 1=self-attested (\u22651 verified factor). 2=multi-factor (\u22652 verified factors across \u22652 distinct classes). 3=covenant-bound (IAL2 + \u22651 covenant-class etzhayyim factor: base-membership / adherent-sbt / at-oath). 4=government-verified (IAL3-or-2 + a verified gov-class factor; Council-attested per ADR-2605260000, gated)."}
 "verifiedFactors" {"type" "array"
 "description" "The SET of distinct verified factorKinds contributing to this credential. Kinds only \u2014 never values/handles/identifiers (G3)."
 "items" {"type" "string"
 "enum" ["webauthn"
 "wallet-evm"
 "wallet-btc"
 "sns-github"
 "sns-x"
 "sns-google"
 "sns-apple"
 "gov-mynumber"
 "gov-passport"
 "gov-license"
 "etz-base-membership"
 "etz-adherent-sbt"
 "etz-at-oath"]}}
 "distinctClasses" {"type" "integer"
 "description" "Number of DISTINCT factor classes among verifiedFactors (device/key/social/government/covenant). The sybil-resistance dimension: two key factors count once."
 "minimum" 0
 "maximum" 5}
 "factorCount" {"type" "integer"
 "description" "Total number of verified factors (verifiedFactors length)."
 "minimum" 0}
 "proofOfPersonhood" {"type" "boolean"
 "description" "True iff assuranceLevel \u2265 2 AND distinctClasses \u2265 2. HONEST framing: this is sybil-RESISTANCE (independent factors raise the cost of a fake identity), NOT sybil-PROOF \u2014 uniqueness-of-human is only approached at IAL 4 (gov-class, Council-gated). Never a ranking of persons (G8)."}
 "issuer" {"type" "string"
 "format" "did"
 "description" "DID that issued the credential. For IAL \u2264 3 = the subject DID (self-issued, re-derivable from public claims). For IAL 4 = the Council-delegated attestor DID (ADR-2605260000)."}
 "issuanceDate" {"type" "integer"
 "description" "Unix timestamp (seconds) of issuance."}
 "expirationDate" {"type" "integer"
 "description" "OPTIONAL Unix timestamp (seconds) of expiry. If present, verifiers reject the credential after it. Recommended for gov-class re-verification cadence."
 "minimum" 0}
 "revoked" {"type" "boolean"
 "description" "OPTIONAL. True if a com.etzhayyim.shomei.bindingRevocation has lowered the assurance below this credential's level since issuance. Append-only: the credential record itself is never mutated (G10 as-of); a fresh credential supersedes it."}
 "proofRef" {"type" "string"
 "description" "OPTIONAL reference (CID or sig) to the subject's signature over this credential (self-issued) or the Council attestation (IAL 4). G7: the server never signs this."
 "maxLength" 256}}}}}}
